text: Thomas Ingler (by 1516 – 26 September 1574), of Linkfield, Reigate, Surrey and the Middle Temple, London, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Reigate in October 1553. ==References== Category:1574 deaths Category:English MPs 1553 (Mary I) Category:People from Surrey Category:Members of the Middle Temple Category:Year of birth uncertain
title: Thomas Ingler
